":"Robertus De Arbalistarius - The Bowman于1126年之前出生在法国諾門迪。他至少有1个儿子。"},"hr":{"before 1126–":"prije 1126.–preminuo","1140–Male":"1140–preminuo","1126–Male":"1126–preminuo","before 1126":"prije 1126.","1126":"1126","1086":"1086","1140":"1140","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Francuska"},"cs":{"before 1126–":"před 1126–Zesnulý","1140–Male":"1140–Zesnulý","1126–Male":"1126–Zesnulý","before 1126":"před 1126","1126":"1126","1086":"1086","1140":"1140","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Francie"},"da":{"before 1126–":"før 1126–Afdød","1140–Male":"1140–Afdød","1126–Male":"1126–Afdød","before 1126":"før 1126","1126":"1126","1086":"1086","1140":"1140","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Frankrig"},"nl":{"before 1126–":"vóór 1126–Overleden","1140–Male":"1140–Overleden","1126–Male":"1126–Overleden","before 1126":"vóór 1126","1126":"1126","1086":"1086","1140":"1140","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Frankrijk"},"en":{"before 1126–":"before 1126–Deceased","1140–Male":"1140–Deceased","1126–Male":"1126–Deceased","before 1126":"before 1126","1126":"1126","1086":"1086","1140":"1140","Normandie, France":"Normandy, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Robertus","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the personal name   Robert  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. This surname is also occasionally borne by Jews, presumably as an Americanized form of some similar (like-sounding) Jewish surname."],"variants":[{"name":"Robert","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."]},{"name":"Robers","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."]},{"name":"Roberds","meanings":["English: variant of   Roberts  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Robards","meanings":["English (Kent): variant of   Roberts  ."]},{"name":"Robarts","meanings":["English (Bedfordshire and Hertfortshire): variant of   Roberts  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Robertus De Arbalistarius - The Bowman was born before 1126, in Normandy, France. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"before 1126–":"enne 1126–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1126–Male":"1126–Surnud","before 1126":"enne 1126","1126":"1126","1086":"1086","1140":"1140","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"before 1126–":"ennen vuotta 1126–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1126–Male":"1126–Kuollut","before 1126":"ennen vuotta 1126","1126":"1126","1086":"1086","1140":"1140","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"before 1126–":"avant 1126–Décédé","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1126–Male":"1126–Décédé","before 1126":"avant 1126","1126":"1126","1086":"1086","1140":"1140","Normandie, France":"Normandie, France","lifeSummary":"Robertus De Arbalistarius - The Bowman est né avant 1126, à Normandie, France. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"before 1126–":"vor 1126–Verstorben","1140–Male":"1140–Verstorben","1126–Male":"1126–Verstorben","before 1126":"vor 1126","1126":"1126","1086":"1086","1140":"1140","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Robertus De Arbalistarius - The Bowman wurde vor 1126 in Normandie, Frankreich geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"before 1126–":"before 1126–Desede","1140–Male":"1140–Desede","1126–Male":"1126–Desede","before 1126":"before 1126","1126":"1126","1086":"1086","1140":"1140","Normandie, France":"Normandie, France"},"hu":{"before 1126–":"1126 előtt–elhunyt","1140–Male":"1140–elhunyt","1126–Male":"1126–elhunyt","before 1126":"1126 előtt","1126":"1126","1086":"1086","1140":"1140","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Franciaország"},"id":{"before 1126–":"sebelum 1126–Telah Meninggal","1140–Male":"1140–Telah Meninggal","1126–Male":"1126–Telah Meninggal","before 1126"